---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/Base.astro';
import NavBar from '@components/scafold/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '@components/scafold/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = '16 June 2026';
const contactEmail = 'abuse@utoggl.in';
const turnstileAddendum =
  'https://www.cloudflare.com/application-services/terms/turnstile-privacy-addendum/';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Web Check"
  description="How this hosted instance of Web Check handles your data."
>
  <div class="web-check-page">
    <NavBar />
    <main>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        This policy explains what happens to data when you use this hosted instance of
        <strong>Web Check</strong>, an open-source tool that inspects the public configuration of a
        website, domain, or IP address you submit. By design, the target you enter is sent to a
        number of third-party lookup services in order to build a report. If you would rather not
        share data with those services, you can
        <a href="https://github.com/uTogglin/web-check">self-host Web Check</a> with your own API
        keys (or none).
      </p>

      <h2>1. What we collect</h2>
      <p>The Service is built to be stateless — no account, no tracking cookies, no database of your scans.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>The target you submit</strong> — the domain, URL, or IP you ask us to check. It is sent to the third-party services below to produce the report.</li>
        <li><strong>Connection metadata</strong> — your IP address, user-agent, and request time, used transiently for rate limiting and the bot-protection check (Section 4). Not stored long-term.</li>
        <li><strong>Aggregate, non-identifying usage stats</strong> — only if analytics are enabled (Section 5).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not knowingly collect personal information about you, and we do not sell any data.</p>

      <h2>2. Where checks run</h2>
      <p>
        Many checks run <strong>directly from your browser</strong> rather than from our servers.
        This is faster, but it means that when a check runs in your browser, your own IP address and
        browser are visible to that third-party API. Other checks run on our backend, in which case
        the third party sees our server instead. Either way, the target you are scanning is shared
        with the relevant services so they can return information about it.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Third-party services that receive scan data</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on which checks run, some or all of the following may receive the target
        domain/URL/IP. Each operates under its own privacy policy, over which we have no control.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Infrastructure:</strong> Cloudflare (CDN, DNS, bot protection) and a third-party cloud hosting provider for the backend API.</p>
      <p><strong>DNS, WHOIS &amp; registry:</strong> Google Public DNS &amp; Cloudflare DNS (DNS-over-HTTPS), rdap.org (RDAP/WHOIS), RIPE NCC (ASN/IP data), crt.sh (Certificate Transparency), Tranco (domain ranking).</p>
      <p><strong>Geolocation:</strong> ipwho.is, geojs.io, reallyfreegeoip.org, ipinfo.io, restcountries.com, flagcdn.com.</p>
      <p><strong>Security &amp; reputation:</strong> Google Safe Browsing, PhishTank, URLhaus / abuse.ch, Shodan, Qualys SSL Labs, Cloudmersive.</p>
      <p><strong>Content &amp; metadata:</strong> Microlink (screenshots), icon.horse (favicons), the Internet Archive (snapshot history).</p>
      <p><strong>Other:</strong> jsonhero.io — only if you explicitly choose to view/share a result's raw JSON.</p>
      <p class="note">
        Web Check also links out to many reference and documentation sites (MDN, OWASP, Wikipedia,
        registrar pages, etc.). Those are ordinary hyperlinks you choose to click; no scan data is
        sent to them automatically.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Bot protection — Cloudflare Turnstile</h2>
      <p>
        To keep this free service available and prevent automated abuse, the Service uses
        <strong>Cloudflare Turnstile</strong> to verify that requests come from a real person. When
        you run a scan, Turnstile runs in the background and may collect data (including your IP
        address and signals about your browser/session) to assess whether you are human. This
        instance uses Turnstile's <strong>invisible</strong> mode; as a condition of that mode we
        are required to point you to Cloudflare's
        <a href={turnstileAddendum} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turnstile Privacy Addendum</a>
        (see also the
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare Privacy Policy</a>).
        Turnstile is designed to be privacy-preserving and does not use the data for advertising or
        cross-site tracking.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        If analytics are enabled on this instance, we use <strong>Plausible Analytics</strong>, a
        privacy-friendly, cookieless tool that collects only aggregate, non-identifying usage
        statistics. It does not track you across sites or store personal data. If disabled, no such
        data is collected.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        The Service does not set advertising or cross-site tracking cookies. Any storage used is
        limited to what is technically necessary to operate the app (for example, a short-lived
        verification token held for the duration of a scan).
      </p>

      <h2>7. Data retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Scan inputs and results are processed on demand and are not persisted in a database by this Service.</li>
        <li>Rate-limiting and bot-protection data is transient and not retained beyond what is needed to operate those protections.</li>
        <li>Third-party services retain data according to their own policies.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. Your choices</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You can <a href="https://github.com/uTogglin/web-check">self-host Web Check</a> to avoid sharing data with this instance.</li>
        <li>You can avoid specific third parties by self-hosting and omitting their API keys.</li>
        <li>Only submit targets you are authorised to inspect; Web Check reports on publicly available configuration only.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy as the Service or its dependencies change. The "Last updated" date above reflects the latest revision.</p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about this policy can be sent to <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.</p>

      <p class="note">
        Web Check is open-source software. This policy covers this particular hosted instance only;
        other deployments may differ.
      </p>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style lang="scss">
  main {
    max-width: 56rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .updated {
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-top: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(127, 127, 127, 0.2);
    padding-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }
  li {
    margin: 0.35rem 0;
  }
  a {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .note {
    opacity: 0.7;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
</style>
